300 1369 1728 (Bjarne's concern is that the behavior of the sum template is changed by the declaration of notify\(char\).) 1728 SB
300 1419 1783 (While I agree that this is unfortunate, it is also a fact of life in C++ as illustrated by the fact that a normal) 1783 SB
300 1469 1660 (\(e.g., nontemplate\) inline member function \(my_class::my_member\) suffers from exactly the same) 1660 SB
300 1519 1763 (problem. Bjarne is further concerned that the behavior of g\(\) is changed  by the declaration of notify\(int\)) 1763 SB
300 1569 1657 (that is included.  Once again, this is unfortunate, but fixing it would take far more than a different) 1657 SB
300 1619 483 (template compilation model.) 483 SB
300 1719 1654 (The name leakage problem affects the following kinds of declarations  in each of the two template) 1654 SB
300 1769 344 (compilation models:) 344 SB
900 1869 174 (separation) 174 SB
1350 1869 155 (inclusion) 155 SB
300 1969 296 (class declarations) 296 SB
900 1969 53 (yes) 53 SB
1350 1969 53 (yes) 53 SB
300 2019 265 (inline functions) 265 SB
900 2019 53 (yes) 53 SB
1350 2019 53 (yes) 53 SB
300 2069 253 (class templates) 253 SB
900 2069 53 (yes) 53 SB
1350 2069 53 (yes) 53 SB
300 2119 421 (inline function templates) 421 SB
900 2119 53 (yes) 53 SB
1350 2119 53 (yes) 53 SB
300 2169 485 (noninline function templates) 485 SB
450 2219 356 (nondependent names) 356 SB
900 2219 42 (no) 42 SB
1350 2219 53 (yes) 53 SB
450 2269 292 (dependent names) 292 SB
900 2269 53 (yes) 53 SB
1350 2269 53 (yes) 53 SB
300 2369 1702 (So, the separation model eliminates name leakage in one of the contexts in which it  occurs, but does) 1702 SB
300 2419 1772 (nothing about all of the other contexts.  I'm not aware of any proposal to try to get rid of name leakage in) 1772 SB
300 2469 1799 (the other contexts, and have seen no explanation why it acceptable in all of those other contexts \(including) 1799 SB
300 2519 1609 (dependent names in function templates\) but is such an awful problem for nondependent names.) 1609 SB
32 0 0 58 58 0 0 0 53 /Helvetica-Bold /font13 ANSIFont font
300 2669 64 (3. ) 78 SB
378 2669 1448 (The separation model has a far more severe problem) 1448 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 2751 1732 (The separation model actually suffers from a form of name leakage far more dangerous and difficult to) 1732 SB
300 2801 1583 (deal with than the one that advocates of the separation model attribute to the inclusion model.) 1583 SB
