300 269 1771 (The separation model actually allows names to "leak" from one translation unit to a  completely different) 1771 SB
300 319 270 (translation unit.) 270 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 46 /Helvetica-BoldOblique /font14 ANSIFont font
300 469 42 (3.) 42 SB
342 469 42 (1 ) 58 SB
400 469 1682 (Introduction to "merged contexts" or "name lookup across translation) 1682 SB
300 528 145 (units") 145 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 650 1736 (This is a consequence of the rules for handling instantiations caused by other  instantiations.  When an) 1736 SB
300 700 1784 (instantiation takes place in the separation model, it takes place in a "merged context" that includes names) 1784 SB
300 750 1799 (from both the translation unit where the template is defined \(let's call it D1\) and the translation unit where) 1799 SB
300 800 1702 (the template was referenced \(let's call it R1\).  Let's call this merged context M1.  If the template then) 1702 SB
300 850 1666 (causes the instantiation of another template defined in a  third translation unit \(let's call it D2\), the) 1666 SB
300 900 1771 (merged context \(let's call it M2\) includes the names from D2 plus the names from the context containing) 1771 SB
300 950 1787 (the template reference,  which in this case is M1 \(the merged context containing names from R1 and D1\).) 1787 SB
300 1000 1641 (This process continues as long as you have templates that themselves call other templates.  If this) 1641 SB
300 1050 1737 (continues for 10 levels, you end up dealing with a merged context that includes 10 different translation) 1737 SB
300 1100 94 (units.) 94 SB
300 1200 1739 (Some people prefer to describe this as a name lookup process that takes place across several translation) 1739 SB
300 1250 1762 (units, instead of calling it context merging.  It really doesn't make any difference, because the results are) 1762 SB
300 1300 885 (the same no matter what name you choose to give it.) 885 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 46 /Helvetica-BoldOblique /font14 ANSIFont font
300 1450 42 (3.) 42 SB
342 1450 42 (2 ) 58 SB
400 1450 895 (Proliferation of instantiation contexts) 895 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 1522 1747 (An interesting property of the separation model is that it creates a proliferation of the contexts in which) 1747 SB
300 1572 1656 (the instantiation of a given function can take place.  The number of possible instantiation contexts) 1656 SB
300 1622 1683 (depends on the various paths through a call graph of the program that can be taken to reach a given) 1683 SB
300 1672 1630 (template, except  that only call graph nodes that represent functions generated from template are) 1630 SB
300 1722 190 (significant.) 190 SB
300 1822 390 (Consider this example:) 390 SB
