300 2191 1681 (And suppose that the implementation chooses to instantiate g\(int\) based on the call found in main\(\)) 1681 SB
300 2241 1796 (instead of the call found in i\(\).  The instantiation context for f\(int\) will now be the context of t2+t1 instead) 1796 SB
300 2291 1771 (of just being the context of t1.  Now, f\(int\) calls h\(int\) instead of h\(char\) despite the fact that h\(int\) is not) 1771 SB
300 2341 1480 (declared in t1.c and the only call of f\(int\) in the entire program is from within  file t1.c!) 1480 SB
